        <div class="body-text" style="max-width:740px;" id="hidden-costs">
          <h3>The hidden costs nobody mentions</h3>

          <p>The plan price is the floor, not the typical bill. Stores running Tidio paid usually pay 2-3x the advertised price. Where the extra goes:</p>

          <p><strong>1. Lyro AI is a separate bill — and it scales fast.</strong> The advertised $24-59/month plans don't include AI. Lyro starts at $32.50-$39 per month for 50 AI conversations and scales by volume up to ~$289/month. Lyro can also run independently of a paid plan at approximately $0.58 per conversation. A typical mid-sized Shopify store using AI ends up with $100+/month just on Lyro before adding the base plan.</p>

          <p><strong>2. Flows are also separately billed.</strong> Tidio's chatbot Flows builder is a separate add-on at $24.17-$29/month for 2,000 reached visitors per month. Pricing is per visitor *reached* by the flow — even if they don't engage. High-traffic stores with prominent flow placement can blow through this allowance fast.</p>

          <p><strong>3. Branding removal is paid.</strong> "Powered by Tidio" appears on Free, Starter, and (without add-on) Growth plans. Removal costs $20/month on Growth, included on Plus and above. For a polished customer-facing brand this is a meaningful extra.</p>

          <p><strong>4. Auto-upgrade at 95% conversation usage.</strong> Unless you disable it, Tidio automatically upgrades your plan when you hit 95% of your conversation quota — and you pay the full higher tier for that month with no proration. If you hit your cap on day 1 of the billing cycle, you pay the full Growth or Plus rate that month. Set internal alerts at 60-70% and disable auto-upgrade if you want manual control.</p>

          <p><strong>5. The Plus tier cliff.</strong> Going from Growth ($49-349/month) to Plus ($749/month) is a brutal jump. The trigger is usually the 11th seat, but it can also be conversation volume above ~5,000/month or features locked behind Plus. There's no smooth scaling between Growth and Plus — it's a $400-700/month vertical cliff.</p>

          <h3>What you actually pay — three real-world examples</h3>

