          <h2 id="vs-h" style="font-size:clamp(28px,4vw,40px);">Where Tidio wins, where it loses</h2>
          <p style="font-size:17px;color:var(--text-3);max-width:640px;">Tidio is excellent for a specific Shopify store profile. These are the cases where alternatives win.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="body-text" style="max-width:740px;">

          <h3>Tidio vs Gorgias — different stages, not different qualities</h3>

          <p>Tidio is built for small-to-medium Shopify stores managing chat and email. Gorgias is built for larger ecommerce stores managing multi-channel high-volume support. Stores grow into Gorgias from Tidio, not the other way around. <a href="/blog/tidio-vs-gorgias-shopify/">The full comparison covers the trigger points.</a></p>

          <p><strong>Use Tidio when:</strong> &lt;$50k/month GMV, &lt;200 conversations/month, chat + email primary, 1-3 agents. <strong>Use Gorgias when:</strong> the opposite — see <a href="/gorgias-shopify-guide/">the Gorgias review</a>.</p>

          <h3>Tidio vs Reamaze — per-agent vs per-conversation</h3>

          <p>Reamaze charges $29-59 per agent per month with strong Shopify integration. For solo founders or 2-agent teams handling moderate conversation volume, Reamaze can be cheaper than Tidio Growth + Lyro + Flows. As teams grow past 4-5 agents, per-agent pricing gets expensive faster than Tidio's conversation-based model.</p>

          <h3>Tidio vs Crisp — when you need a clean free plan</h3>

          <p>Crisp's free plan is strong for chat alone (unlimited conversations on the free tier, 2 agents) but lacks Tidio's Shopify-native integration. For solo founders who want chat-only without paying anything, Crisp is genuinely better than Tidio's free plan. Once you need ticketing, multi-channel, or AI, Tidio pulls ahead.</p>

          <h3>Tidio vs Chatra — solo founder simplicity</h3>

          <p>Chatra has a permanent free plan with 1 agent and a single chat widget. For a one-person Shopify store that just wants a chat widget, Chatra is simpler than Tidio. Tidio wins as soon as you need email integration, social channels, or any automation.</p>

