          <details style="background:var(--bg-3);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:20px 24px;">
            <summary style="cursor:pointer;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--text);">Does Tidio have a free plan?</summary>
            <div style="margin-top:12px;font-size:15px;color:var(--text-2);line-height:1.65;">
              <p>Yes — Tidio's free plan is genuinely useful, not a gated demo. 50 billable conversations/month, 10 agent seats, live chat, ticketing, and 50 one-time Lyro AI conversations as a lifetime trial. There is also a 7-day free trial of all premium features with no credit card. The free plan reverts after the trial ends. The 50-conversation cap is the main constraint.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details style="background:var(--bg-3);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:20px 24px;">
            <summary style="cursor:pointer;font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--text);">What counts as a billable conversation in Tidio?</summary>
            <div style="margin-top:12px;font-size:15px;color:var(--text-2);line-height:1.65;">
              <p>Any chat, ticket, email, or social thread where a human agent replies at least once. If a customer messages and no human responds, it's not billed. Lyro AI replies and Flows do not count as human replies. Each new chat session is a separate billable conversation, including returning customers. Quotas refresh every 30 days from your billing date and unused capacity does not roll over.</p>
